(      configs/                 config loading, state, shared config types) Tj
T*
(      incubating/factory/      factory schemas, cards, packs \(future separate repo\)) Tj
T*
(      test/mocks/              test doubles) Tj
T*
(      docs/                    architecture, plans, and backlog) Tj
T*
T*
(Primary Runtime Flow) Tj
T*
T*
(    cmd/ms-cli) Tj
T*
(      -> internal/app.Run\(...\)) Tj
T*
(      -> internal/app.Wire\(...\)) Tj
T*
(      -> ui.New\(...\)) Tj
T*
T*
(    user input) Tj
T*
(      -> internal/app.processInput\(...\)) Tj
T*
(      -> slash command \(/train, /diagnose, /factory status, ...\)) Tj
T*
(         or free text -> runTask\(...\)) Tj
T*
T*
(    runTask:) Tj
T*
(      -> compose effective system prompt:) Tj
T*
(           EngineConfig.SystemPrompt) Tj
T*
(           + skill summaries \(from integrations/skills\)) Tj
T*
(           + active skill SKILL.md \(if command-scoped\)) Tj
T*
(      -> agent/loop.Engine.RunWithContext\(task\)) Tj
T*
(      -> tools.Registry) Tj
T*
(      -> tools/fs or tools/shell) Tj
T*
(      -> runtime/shell.Runner) Tj
T*
(      -> loop.Event stream -> model.Event -> ui) Tj
T*
T*
(No orchestrator, no planner, no adapter layer. The app calls the engine) Tj
T*
(directly. The LLM plans inline within the agent loop.) Tj
T*
T*
(Skill activation) Tj
T*
T*
(Skills are command-scoped. No sticky state.) Tj
T*
T*
(    /diagnose my training crashed) Tj
T*
(      -> app loads failure-agent SKILL.md from integrations/skills) Tj
T*
(      -> sets task.SkillContext \(one task only\)) Tj
T*
(      -> engine composes effective system prompt: base + active skill) Tj
T*
(      -> engine runs) Tj
T*
(      -> next task has no skill context \(base prompt only\)) Tj
T*
T*
(Free text uses the base system prompt which includes skill summaries) Tj
T*
(\(name + one-line description\). The LLM has awareness of available) Tj
T*
(capabilities but this is not deterministic routing -- for reliable skill) Tj
T*
(activation, use explicit commands.) Tj
T*
T*
(Train mode) Tj
ET
endstream
