(- configs/ Shared configuration types and loaders.) Tj
T*
T*
(Dependency Boundaries) Tj
T*
T*
(    cmd/ms-cli -> internal/app) Tj
T*
(    internal/app -> agent, workflow, ui, configs, integrations, tools, permission, trace) Tj
T*
(    agent -> integrations, permission, configs, trace) Tj
T*
(    workflow -> internal/train, runtime/probes, configs) Tj
T*
(    tools -> runtime, integrations, configs) Tj
T*
(    runtime -> configs) Tj
T*
(    ui -> configs) Tj
T*
(    report -> trace, configs) Tj
T*
T*
(Constraints:) Tj
T*
T*
(- cmd/ms-cli/ stays thin.) Tj
T*
(- internal/app/ is the wiring layer, not a reusable core package.) Tj
T*
(- agent/ must not depend on ui/ or runtime/ directly.) Tj
T*
(- workflow/train/ must not import ui/model; conversion belongs in) Tj
T*
(  internal/app/train.go.) Tj
T*
(- tools/ may call runtime/, but runtime/ must not call tools/.) Tj
T*
(- configs/ is shared configuration, not a home for application logic.) Tj
T*
T*
(Removed Packages \(refactor\)) Tj
T*
T*
(The following packages are removed by the refactor \(see) Tj
T*
(docs/ms-cli-refactor.md\):) Tj
T*
T*
(- agent/orchestrator/ -- was a dispatch layer between planner and) Tj
T*
(  executors. After removing workflow mode, it became a passthrough. The) Tj
T*
(  app now calls the engine directly.) Tj
T*
(- agent/planner/ -- was an LLM-based plan generator that decided agent vs) Tj
T*
(  workflow mode. Standard agent loops don't have a separate planner; the) Tj
T*
(  LLM plans inline. Skill selection uses explicit commands, not an LLM) Tj
T*
(  pre-call.) Tj
T*
(- workflow/executor/ -- was a workflow execution framework \(demo JSON) Tj
T*
(  playback) Tj
T*
(  - stub\). Never developed beyond demo. Train mode uses its own) Tj
T*
(    controller.) Tj
T*
(- internal/app/adapter.go -- was a type converter between orchestrator) Tj
T*
(  and engine event types. No longer needed with direct engine calls.) Tj
T*
(- demo/scenarios/ -- JSON scenario files for workflow demo playback.) Tj
T*
T*
(Related Docs) Tj
T*
T*
(- docs/ms-cli-refactor.md -- refactor plan \(workstream A\)) Tj
T*
(- docs/ms-skills-update-plan.md -- skills plan \(workstream B\)) Tj
